(120, 1, '2019-03-27 21:18:04', '2019-03-27 21:18:04', 'In the 1990s, theoretical physicist Klaus Lackner had an idea. Was it possible to build a contraption that physically sucked greenhouse gases out of the atmosphere? At the time, the idea was radical. Some people thought it was nuts. Two decades later, many of the experts have come around to Lackners view. Pulling carbon from the air is now seen as crucial, and Lackner has created such a machine.', 'Saving the world from thin air', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'saving-the-world-from-thin-air', '', '', '2019-04-03 21:28:24', '2019-04-03 21:28:24', '', 0, 'https://globalfutures.asu.edu/?p=120', 0, 'post', '', 0),
